commit.message: Removing the 'redirect_stdout' in favor of 'print(..., file=stream)'
Checking for subclass of IOBase was a nice thought, but won't translate
Add support for sending output to something besides stdout

Use @functools.wraps() instead of open-coding it

This also sets __wrapped__ properly, which should make our decorators
play more nicely with other decorators.

Correctly detect Python source file encoding

Using open() on a Python source file will not work if the system locale
doesn't match the source file encoding.  Let's use tokenize.open()
instead which will look for # -*- coding: ... -*- declarations and such.

Closes #24.

Also drop very outdated Python 2.3 (!) code examples from the module
docstring.

Looks like specifying source in .coveragerc breaks coveralls

Currently coveralls shows 93% because some jobs are at 100% but others
are at 76%, and coveralls has trouble aggregating them.

Test coverage is not 100% on Python 3

Because hotshot was removed.  (TBH I should remove it from Python 2 too.)

Stay tuned to https://travis-ci.community/t/add-python-3-8-support/5463.
